<entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"
    xml:id="entry_bæǧæmsar" xml:lang="os">
    <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>bæǧæmsar</orth></form>
    <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>bæǧænsar</orth></form>
    <sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
            <q>с непокрытой головой</q>
        </cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
            <q>bare-headed</q>
        </cit></sense>
    <cit type="exampleGroup">
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>Axmæt bæǧæmsuræj fæsdwar wyrdyg læwwydī</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>Ахмат с непокрытой головой стоял за дверью</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>Ahmat stood bare-headed behind the door</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl><ref target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>60</biblScope></bibl>
        </cit>
    </cit>
    <cit type="exampleGroup">
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>Axmæt bæǧæmsuræj fæsdwar wyrdyg læwwydī</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>Ахмат с непокрытой головой стоял за дверью</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>Ahmat stood bare-headed behind the door</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl><ref target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>60</biblScope></bibl>
        </cit>
    </cit>
    <etym xml:lang="ru">Из %ibæǧnæ%i-%isur%i ← <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"
                ><lang/><w>*maǧna-sāra-</w></mentioned>. Подъем гласного во второй части сложного
        слова (%især%i → %isar%i) обычен (композиционное %ivṛddhi%i), ср. raj-ʒast ‘светлый’ [см.
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_rajʒast"/>] (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_cæst"/>
        ‘глаз’), don-ʒaw ‘водонос’ [см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_donʒaw"/> ] (<ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_cæwyn"/> ‘идти’), ʒiʒi-daj ‘сосун’ [см. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_ʒiʒidaj"/>] (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_dæjyn"/> ‘сосать грудь’). —
        См. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bæǧnæg"/> ‘голый’ и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sær"/>
        ‘голова’; ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bæǧæmzæng"/>.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
            /></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">From %ibæǧnæ%i-%isur%i ← <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"
                ><lang/><w>*maǧna-sāra-</w></mentioned>. Vowel alternation in the second part of the
        complex word (%især%i → %isar%i) is regular (compositional %ivṛddhi%i), cf. %iraj-ʒast%i
        ‘light’ [see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_rajʒast"/>] (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_cæst"
        /> ‘eye’), %idon-ʒaw%i ‘water carrier’ [see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_donʒaw"/> ] (<ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_cæwyn"/> ‘go’), %iʒiʒi-daj%i ‘suckling’ [see <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_ʒiʒidaj"/>] (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_dæjyn"/> ‘suck the breast'). —
        See <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bæǧnæg"/> ‘bare’ and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sær"/>
        ‘head’; cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bæǧæmzæng"/>.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>29</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
